text:
09 New York City to offer low-cost healthcare to uninsured immigrants 
Reuters: New York will become one of the first major U.S. cities to expand low-cost healthcare to uninsured immigrants regardless of their legal status under a pilot program to launch next spring, Mayor Bill de Blasio said on Thursday.
